#X text 23 63 The [adsr~] object has an attack \, a decay \, a sustain point and release stage. It has even more features and is quite more comples and versatile than [asr~] (which can be considered a simplified version of it). We can just use the 'release' phase of it and it'll be the same as the last example with [asr~]. But note that this will only worl for impulses \, not gates. The arguments set the attack \, decay \, sustain point and release parameters. Below \, we just have a release parameter \, so an impulse goes straigth to it., f 46;
