#X text 43 502 Nonetheless \, there's a way to make [adsr~] work with gates as well as impulses. We just need to set the decay time the same as the release time. The sustain point must remain zero \, then a fixed gate on value just dies away and goes to a null sustain value. This way \, if you also turn of the gate before the decay stage \, it moves to the release stage and continues to die away. Check on the example to the right on the top how both an impulse and/or a gate will just work., f 42;
#X text 382 19 Note that like [asr~] \, [adsr~] also has curve parameters and a lag mode., f 41;
#X text 368 330 There's a way to just work with gates and ignore the release stage. You have to set a minimum sustain period of 0 (default is -1). This way it will always reach the sustain point \, no matter what \, check the help file for more details)., f 44;
